A) If installed via apt (using a repository)
1)Run the following command to remove Terraform:
sudo apt-get remove --purge terraform
2)Then, clean up any leftover dependencies:
sudo apt-get autoremove
B)2. If installed via a binary (manual install):
If Terraform was installed by downloading the binary and placing it in a directory like /usr/local/bin, you can remove it by:
sudo rm /usr/local/bin/terraform
3. Verify removal:
terraform --version

